description:
&lt;p&gt;Moorfields Bank are seeking an experienced Theatre Manager on a temporary basis to cover an initial 4 month vacancy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Moorfields NHS Foundation Trust is a world leading single speciality organisation and centre of excellence. The Trust provides high quality care across a range of ophthalmic specialities working in partnership with University College London Institute of Ophthalmology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The City Road Division is the main hospital site for the Trust and in our most recent published report from the Care Quality Commission (CQC), has been given a rating of “Outstanding” and ‘Good’ overall for the Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a highly experienced, dynamic, energetic and motivated registered practitioner or experienced operational manager, who is able to provide demonstrable evidence of having lead and managed complex and high volume theatre departments and services beyond.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible for managing the theatre leadership team, sterile service manager and support in quality improvement pathways across the surgical patient pathway. You will expect a high degree of autonomy and work within and across a number of services, departments and professional groups across the Moorfield’s network.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you hold the below requirements please apply today:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A Current NMC or HCPC Registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience in a theatre practice at a band 8a or above&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of staff management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of budget management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is full time and interviews will be held week commencing 26thOctober.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
